[
  "Dani Reiss took over as CEO of outerwear company Canada Goose in 2001.",
  "His grandfather, a Polish immigrant, launched the Toronto-based retailer as Metro Sportswear in 1957.",
  "Today the company is known for its down jackets, which cost over $1,000 and are a favorite among celebrities like Bradley Cooper and Emma Stone.",
  "Reiss took Canada Goose public in March 2017; he owns about 18% of the stock.",
  "He has pledged to keep manufacturing in Canada and employs more than 3,400 people."
